Also important is speed, the number of frames per second.
Human movements are quite dynamic and the current 30 fps movements are really scarce, especially for gestures.
Steven Bathiche, from our laboratory in Redmond, made a contact sensor with adjustable processing delay of 1 to 100 ms and it should be mentioned that modern serial-produced sensors are closer to the second value (60-100).
