Manning said he always had a light coming from outside pointing to his eyes while he was asleep.
He said that if the lockers couldn't see his face when he turned around at night, they would wake him up to turn around again.
Manning's lawyer filed in January 2011 a formal claim on the treatment that Manning received.
Manning was transferred to Fort Leavenworth military prison in Kansas in April 2011.
On Friday, the judge asked Manning about a claim he had made in his statement on Thursday that, after having been forced to sleep naked in his Quantico cell, he was forced to stand naked in front of the lockers and other prisoners during a morning count.
Manning had testified that he had never been given the opportunity to cover himself with the blanket during the count.
