Then he sells it for 10,000 rupees (83 cents of euro) to the petrochemical industry, as this mineral is widespread in everyday life and is used to manufacture waxes, artificial fires, cosmetics, dynamite and even to bleach sugar.
"As usual it is to load 70 kilos, we take about 46,000 rupees (3,8 euros) on each trip," explains Anto, who usually carries three daily doors.
